# 4. 似た者同士

Honami: “Just wait. I promise to find a star that will grant my wish.”
Nene: Oh... I really like the way you said that just now.
Nene: You made this dog sound so kind. The way he comforted the boy felt so genuine.
Honami: Really? Thank goodness...!
Nene: This dog really reminds me of you, Mochizuki. I feel like your voice is perfect for him.
Honami: Oh, that's what MEI... I mean, that's what Ichika and the others told me. This dog also reminded them of me.
Nene: Hehe. I can see why.
Honami: After actually giving it a try, I realized how difficult this really is...
Honami: And I'd probably still be lost if you hadn't agreed to coach me, Kusanagi.
Nene: I'm glad you're saying that, since I'm no voice acting expert myself. I'm honestly stumbling around in the dark a bit here...
Honami: Hehe. You gave me a wonderful explanation.
Honami: I know that I have a lot to learn since my acting skills are still quite poor...
Honami: But I plan on doing my best to make sure all those children go home smiling.
Nene: ...
Nene: And I wouldn't expect anything less from you, Mochizuki...
Honami: Huh?
Nene: Because you're always working for the sake of others. Whenever you see someone in need, you never hesitate to jump in and help them.
Honami: Yes, my primary goal is to make sure the children enjoy this story...
Honami: But that isn't actually the reason I decided to do this.
Nene: It isn't?
Honami: *Nod* I've never forgotten how moved I was when I had this story read to me for the very first time.
Honami: I remember being so worried when the dog decided to set out on his journey to save the boy...
Honami: And by the time he did save the boy, I was bawling my eyes out.
Nene: I see. In other words, this story means just that much to you, yes?
Honami: It does. I quickly fell in love with picture books, and I discovered many more wonderful stories soon after.
Honami: Which is why I'd like the children to experience the same thing I did...
Nene: I know what you mean...
Nene: I remember being really moved by this show I saw when I was little...
Nene: I first fell in love with shows, and I subsequently fell in love with singing and acting.
Honami: I had no idea...!
Nene: At first, I simply wanted to become just like the lead actress I saw on stage.
Nene: But as time went on, that feeling transformed into a desire to make others feel that same sense of exhilaration.
Honami: That's so wonderful...
Nene: I mean, that's basically what you just said. So...
Nene: I feel like we're in the same boat here.
Honami: Hehe. We are.
Nene: In that case... I don't know if you'd be okay with it, but...
Nene: Is it possible for people from outside your neighborhood to help with this event?
Honami: Wait, does that mean...?
Nene: I feel like taking part now after hearing your story, Mochizuki...
Honami: Thank you! Having you there would make me feel so much better, Kusanagi!
Honami: I'll need to ask the association for permission, but it shouldn't be a problem.
Nene: Okay, that's good to hear...
Honami: If we'll both be reading, should we divide up the roles between us?
Nene: Oh, if you wanna do that, then I have a suggestion...
Nene: I think you should play the dog, Mochizuki.
Honami: Wait, you want me playing the lead...?
Nene: Yes. I know it won't be easy because there are so many lines, but I really do think your gentle voice fits the bill...
Honami: Oh...
Honami: Thank you. Then, I'll do my best...!
Nene: Okay, I'll also help out however I can.
Nene: Anyway, let's start dividing up the other roles.
Honami: Okay!
Honami: Kusanagi...
Nene: Yeah?
Honami: I look forward to working with you on this.
Nene: Hehe. Me too...
